h3. Issue Summary
* Whenever using non-utf8 characters inside source files, the UI won't be able to load the diff due to this character and throw a generic *Something went wrong message*;
* This issue is also associated with the following error message:
{code}UnicodeDecodeError: 'utf8' codec can't decode byte 0xa9 in position 743: invalid start byte{code}

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Add a non-utf8 character to any source file, eg. the copyright symbol ©;
 # Try to load that file's diff through the UI;

h3. Expected Results
 * UI should be able to correctly display the diff regardless of the special character;

h3. Actual Results
 * UI displays a *Something went wrong* error message;

h3. Workaround
As a workaround to this issue, it is either possible to:
# Remove the special character from the file's source; or
# View the diff locally using:
{code}$ git diff <target-branch>...<source-branch> -- path/to/file.txt{code}

h3. Issue Summary
* Branch permissions which patterns start with a "/" eg. */release/**, causes UI actions not to work, such as editing and deleting the branch permissions.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a branch permission with a pattern beginning with "/" eg. */release/**
 # Try to update it or delete it;

h3. Expected Results
* Brach permission should be correctly updated or deleted;

h3. Actual Results
* Due to the initial "/", the API call does not delete or update the branch permissions;

h3. Workaround
It is still possible to delete the branch permission leveraging the [2.0 API|https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/resource/repositories/%7Bworkspace%7D/%7Brepo_slug%7D/branch-restrictions/%7Bid%7D],  as it uses the branch restriction ID:
# Get a list of branch permissions ID's: {code}$ curl --request GET \
  --url https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/<WorkspaceID>/<Repo-Slug>/branch-restrictions?pagelen=100 \
  --user "<username>:<AppPassword>"{code}
# Delete the desired branch restriction:
{code}
curl --request DELETE \
  --url https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/<WorkspaceID>/<Repo-Slug>/branch-restrictions/<branch-restriction-id>\
  --user "<username>:<AppPassword>"
{code}

h3. Issue Summary
 * Currently, diffs are being generated using short hashes for blobs/commits, so when checking commits/diffs, Bitbucket might generate a *Something went wrong* message.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 * As this is completely at random depending on the OIDs generated by git inside a repository, there are no steps to reproduce it;

h3. Expected Results
 * Commit HASH should be longer to avoid hash ambiguity;

h3. Actual Results
 * First 7 characters of the commit Hash coincidentally might have an exact match that will trigger an  error as a result of ambiguity;

h3. Workaround
 * End users can use GIT Diff to review the diff locally using complete commit HASH/blob OID;
